The paper discusses advancements in few-shot learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on modifications to the Model Agnostic Meta Learning (MAML) algorithm, which is commonly used in few-shot learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
